        <num>CC 2433</num>
        <heading>2433.  Incident of marriage; charge on the succession</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2433.  Incident of marriage; charge on the succession.
The marital portion is an incident of any matrimonial regime and a charge on the succession of the deceased spouse.  It may be claimed by the surviving spouse, even if separated from the deceased, on proof that the separation occurred without his fault.</p>
        </content>
